# 12_toolbar_popovers — exercise the s195 m5 toolbar-popover substrate.
#
# Confirms the zoom popover's preset buttons and the snap-options
# popover's six category checkboxes are addressable via the script
# DSL. Pre-s195 these were raw Gtk widgets with set_name'd abbrevs
# (visible to widget_names.db, invisible to the script registry);
# s195 m5 migrated them to curvz::widgets::* substrate so the
# abbrevs resolve in the registry too.
#
# The tested abbrevs:
#
#   Zoom popover  pop_tb_zom_p25 / p50 / p100 / p200 / p400
#                 pop_tb_zom_fit
#                 pop_tb_zom_apl
#
#   Snap popover  pop_tb_snap_g  (guides)
#                 pop_tb_snap_gr (grid)
#                 pop_tb_snap_m  (margins)
#                 pop_tb_snap_n  (nodes)
#                 pop_tb_snap_e  (edges)
#                 pop_tb_snap_c  (centers)
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.
#
# Side effects: the script flips snap categories during the run and
# restores them at the end. If you have non-default snap settings
# they may get clobbered (the script restores from a hard-coded
# state, not from a captured baseline).

#[sub] Snap-to-guides toggles.

pop_tb_snap_g set true
assert pop_tb_snap_g active == true
pop_tb_snap_g set false
assert pop_tb_snap_g active == false

#[sub] Snap-to-grid toggles.

pop_tb_snap_gr set true
assert pop_tb_snap_gr active == true
pop_tb_snap_gr set false
assert pop_tb_snap_gr active == false

#[sub] Snap-to-margins toggles.

pop_tb_snap_m set true
assert pop_tb_snap_m active == true
pop_tb_snap_m set false
assert pop_tb_snap_m active == false

#[sub] Snap-to-nodes toggles.

pop_tb_snap_n set true
assert pop_tb_snap_n active == true
pop_tb_snap_n set false
assert pop_tb_snap_n active == false

#[sub] Snap-to-edges toggles.

pop_tb_snap_e set true
assert pop_tb_snap_e active == true
pop_tb_snap_e set false
assert pop_tb_snap_e active == false

#[sub] Snap-to-centers toggles.

pop_tb_snap_c set true
assert pop_tb_snap_c active == true
pop_tb_snap_c set false
assert pop_tb_snap_c active == false

#[sub] Zoom presets — labels read back from the registry.

assert pop_tb_zom_p25 label == "25%"
assert pop_tb_zom_p50 label == "50%"
assert pop_tb_zom_p100 label == "100%"
assert pop_tb_zom_p200 label == "200%"
assert pop_tb_zom_p400 label == "400%"

#[sub] Fit and Apply labels.

assert pop_tb_zom_fit label == "Fit"
assert pop_tb_zom_apl label == "Apply"

#[sub] Click the 100% preset (sets zoom_adj, doesn't apply yet).

pop_tb_zom_p100 click

#[sub] Done. 13 new substrate widgets, all addressable.
